The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 April is 41,913 (4,851.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 April, there were 130 new confirmed cases (15.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 April, there were 136 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (6 fewer cases).
